---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="About - Tech Blog" 
  description="Learn more about this blog and its mission"
>
  <article class="about-page" data-astro-transition-scope="about">
    <h1>About This Blog</h1>
    
    <section>
      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>
        This blog is dedicated to exploring the latest trends in web development,
        sharing knowledge about modern technologies, and documenting best practices
        in software engineering. We believe in creating content that is both
        educational and practical.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Built with Astro</h2>
      <p>
        This site is built using <strong>Astro</strong>, a modern static site generator
        that delivers lightning-fast performance by shipping minimal JavaScript to the
        browser. Astro allows us to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Generate static HTML at build time for optimal performance</li>
        <li>Use components from any framework (React, Vue, Svelte, etc.)</li>
        <li>Leverage the View Transition API for smooth page transitions</li>
        <li>Create reusable layouts and components for consistent design</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>View Transitions</h2>
      <p>
        This site implements the <strong>View Transition API</strong> to provide
        seamless transitions between pages. Notice how smoothly content transitions
        when navigating between different pages - this is powered by Astro's built-in
        View Transitions support.
      </p>
      <p>
        The View Transition API allows for smooth, app-like transitions in a
        multi-page application (MPA) context, providing a better user experience
        without the complexity of a single-page application (SPA).
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        Have questions or suggestions? Feel free to explore our blog posts or
        reach out through your preferred channel.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 3rem;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .about-page h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #8B0000 0%, #6B0000 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .about-page section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .about-page h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #1a1a1a;
  }

  .about-page p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #333;
  }

  .about-page ul {
    margin-left: 2rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .about-page li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: #333;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-page {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    .about-page h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>

